🧠 What is Event Loop?

Event Loop is the **core mechanism** that allows Node.js to:

👉 Handle multiple operations using **single thread**

```text
Single Thread + Async Operations = High Performance 🚀
````

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Why Event Loop is Important?

Without Event Loop:

❌ Blocking code execution
❌ Slow performance
❌ Cannot handle multiple users

With Event Loop:

✔ Non-blocking execution
✔ Handles thousands of requests
✔ Efficient performance

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Key Components of Event Loop

1️⃣ Call Stack
2️⃣ Web APIs / Node APIs
3️⃣ Callback Queue
4️⃣ Event Loop

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 1️⃣ Call Stack

👉 Executes functions **one by one (LIFO)**

```javascript
function a() {
  b();
}

function b() {
  console.log("Inside B");
}

a();
```

✔ Executes in order

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 2️⃣ Callback Queue

👉 Stores async callbacks

```javascript
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("Timer done");
}, 2000);
```

✔ Goes to queue after delay

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 3️⃣ Event Loop Working

```text
Check Call Stack
   ↓
If empty → Take from Callback Queue
   ↓
Push to Call Stack
   ↓
Execute
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Example: Event Loop Execution

```javascript
console.log("Start");

setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("Async Task");
}, 0);

console.log("End");
```

🧾 Output:

```text
Start
End
Async Task
```

✔ Because async goes to queue first

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Microtasks vs Macrotasks ⭐

🔹 Microtasks (High Priority)

✔ Promise.then()
✔ process.nextTick()

🔹 Macrotasks

✔ setTimeout()
✔ setInterval()

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Example: Micro vs Macro

```javascript
console.log("Start");

setTimeout(() => console.log("Timeout"), 0);

Promise.resolve().then(() => console.log("Promise"));

console.log("End");
```

🧾 Output:

```text
Start
End
Promise
Timeout
```

✔ Microtasks execute first

