🔷 Async Example (Real-World)

```javascript
const fs = require("fs");

fs.readFile("file.txt", () => {
  console.log("File Read Done");
});

console.log("Reading...");
```

🧾 Output:

```text
Reading...
File Read Done
```

✔ Non-blocking I/O

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Blocking vs Non-Blocking

🔴 Blocking:

```javascript
const data = fs.readFileSync("file.txt");
```

🟢 Non-Blocking:

```javascript
fs.readFile("file.txt", callback);
```

✔ Always prefer async

